# HTML Structure Guidelines

## Timeline Section Template
Each timeline section follows this structure in [index.html](mdc:index.html):

```html
<section class="timeline-section" id="section-id">
    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
    <div class="timeline-content">
        <div class="timeline-card">
            <div class="card-header">
                <h2 class="chapter-title">Title</h2>
                <span class="chapter-date">Date Range</span>
            </div>
            <div class="card-image">
                <div class="illustration-placeholder">
                    <span class="placeholder-text">Pencil Illustration</span>
                    <div class="placeholder-icon">✏️</div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p class="chapter-description">Description text</p>
                <div class="chapter-tags">
                    <span class="tag">Tag1</span>
                    <span class="tag">Tag2</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
```

## Semantic HTML
- Use semantic section elements for each timeline chapter
- Proper heading hierarchy (h1 for hero, h2 for chapter titles)
- Descriptive IDs for timeline sections
- Alt text for all images (when added)

## Accessibility
- Maintain proper heading structure
- Use descriptive link text
- Ensure sufficient color contrast
- Include skip navigation for keyboard users

## Content Guidelines
- Chapter titles should be concise and descriptive
- Date ranges should be clear and consistent
- Descriptions should be engaging and personal
- Tags should be relevant and consistent across sections